File: Over 4.5 million coronavirus tests have been completed. AFP/Douglas Magno JOHANNESBURG - The Health Department reported 72 more people have succumbed to COVID-19. According to the department, seven of the new deaths occurred in the past 24 to 48 hours. The COVID-19 death toll in South Africa is at 19,749. There have been 1,761 new reported cases. READ: Gauteng acting-Health MEC promises to prioritise stability The cumulative number of detected COVID-19 cases in SA is 734,175. Recoveries in SA are at 675, 593. The recovery rate is 92-percent. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.